## The 4 Oval Halo Styles: What Each One Actually Does

### Single Halo (Classic)

One row of round brilliant micro-pavé diamonds following the oval perimeter. This is the default halo — the highest review counts, widest price range ($1,370–$5,985), and the most forgiving design across center stone sizes. The [Falling Edge Pavé Halo by JA](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/falling-edge-pave-halo-engagement-ring-in-14k-yellow-gold-by-james-allen-item-311115?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) at 368 reviews is the reference single halo.

### Double Halo

Two concentric rows of accent diamonds — inner halo and outer halo. Creates maximum face-up diamond coverage. Requires 2ct+ center stone. Available at Blue Nile as the [Micropavé Double Halo](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/micropave-double-halo-engagement-ring-in-14k-yellow-gold-item-146207?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) ($2,605) and the [Blue Nile Studio Double Halo Gala](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/the-gala-halo-engagement-ring-in-18k-yellow-gold-item-203781?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) ($5,985).

### Hidden Halo

Accent diamonds are set beneath the girdle of the center stone rather than around its top perimeter. Viewed from above, the ring looks like a solitaire. Viewed from the side or at an angle, a ring of diamonds is visible beneath the stone — sparkle without surface area. This is the professional's halo: understated in formal settings, visually interesting up close. Blue Nile offers two: the [Lace Bridge Hidden Halo](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/lace-bridge-hidden-halo-engagement-ring-in-14k-yellow-gold-item-197057?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) ($1,745) and the [X Split Shank Hidden Halo](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/x-split-shank-hidden-halo-engagement-ring-in-14k-yellow-gold-item-192268?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) ($3,040).

### Marquise Halo

Instead of round accent diamonds, the halo uses marquise-cut accent stones pointing outward from the oval perimeter — a starburst or sunburst silhouette. The elongated marquise diamonds visually extend the ring's outline and create a shape that reads as distinctly non-standard. The [Marquise Accent Halo by JA](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/marquise-accent-halo-engagement-ring-in-14k-yellow-gold-by-james-allen-item-305244?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) ($1,630) is the only marquise halo for oval diamonds at Blue Nile. Nothing else in the collection looks like it.

